                     <interp inst="t17900424-10-person105" type="gender" value="female"></interp>
                  </persName>
             sworn.</p>
               <p>I am a pawn-broker: I live at No. 19, Little Britain: I took in a table-spoon on Saturday, the 3d of April, between six and seven in the evening; the prisoner brought it; I had seen him several times before; I lent him five shillings upon it; he said it was not his own; I have had it ever since.</p>
               <p>(Produces it.)</p>
               <p>Silk. This is my spoon; it is marked I. S.; it is one that was missing.</p>
               <p>Court. Did you give him any authority to pawn it? - No, Sir.</p>
               <p>Did you ask him any thing about it? - He acknowledged taking it.</p>
               <p>PRISONER's DEFENCE.</p>
               <p>This spoon was in the yard among some rubbish: I expected three witnesses; they are not come.</p>
               <p>
                  <rs id="t17900424-10-verdict60" type="verdictDescription">
                     <interp inst="t17900424-10-verdict60" type="verdictCategory" value="guilty"></interp>
               GUILTY
            </rs>.</p>
